item.title: A friend experienced with these guys just told me this. I promise I am not stringing you along. We are learning together. Incubating at a lower temperature is not a bad thing (as long as it's not too low)! In fact, it helps prevent kinks and other issues.
item.description: Sharing advice from a friend about why slightly lower incubation temps can actually be better for healthy hatchlings.
